day_1.highlights: Noticing my body through the different exercises.
day_1.improvements: Normalising thoughts, experiences, reactions that might come about in a group. Some people may need to release tears or emotions and so what is available for them during the experience…

-since the study is unblinded anyway, share the research hypothesis with participants; -1:1 interpret individual and group results with participants; -offer participant compensation; -control for more variables: sitting, blindfold, etc; -don’t bias participants with a presentation before the experiment

day_1.highlights: The rising spotlight on energy, vibration, resonance, music, art & joy & the technology finally able to quantify their impact.
day_1.improvements: Can’t think of a thing that I would change.

day_1.highlights: The live violin was extraordinary. I also really liked the meditations where we focused on the energy of the heart.
day_1.improvements: Maybe start a little later so you have time to properly prep and participants don’t have to show up so early. A communal lunch would be nice too as I have the energy of the room building but it scattered a bit at lunch.

day_1.highlights: I really enjoyed the correlations between the universe, and our own neuro make up. I’m fascinated to continue exploring what Studies can be done around Intercultural neural residence, as well as inter practice or in George spiritual.
day_1.improvements: I’d really like to see and be a part of studies around melanated individuals working in dominantly none Melanated spaces and to track the heart rate of the individual who is the minority.  I’d like to emphasize this as a metaphor for the micro macro correlation.   I’d also like to do series of Studies around pre-conceived, stigma around Plant Medicine, and how that effects the ability of the individuals with pre conceived stigmas to receive the benefits in a shared space. For example, if someone thought that someone else in the space was going to tempt them out of their sobriety with , does it effect their ability to find cohesion.   How does visual representation effect heart rate in wellness spaces   brain mapping and the tests of black students flowing around other black students verse flowing with non black   How does hip hop and yoga effect the brain in correlation

day_1.highlights: Realizing how seamlessly your work integrates music, embodiment, and technology, and how aligned that is with several of my own creative projects.
day_1.improvements: The day was extremely well designed. One idea for future studies would be exploring additional sensory inputs (like scent or taste) to deepen the embodied, emotional dimension of the experience.

day_1.emotional_words: More connected with thinking mind again , calm, flow
day_1.highlights: Breathwork with binaural beats, presentation by Dr. Mitch Abraham
day_1.improvements: Nothing specific yet, only curious to see other tests with different breathwork facilitators and music

day_2.highlights: A second day of immersive medicina experiencing + it having a desired outcome to improve the likelihood of this work being accesible is a good feeling :

day_2.improvements: Space to relax and connect to the work

day_2.highlights: I loved how coming back together for a second day was like getting together with people I’ve known for a lifetime, as though we hadn’t just met yesterday.
day_2.improvements: Same observation as yesterday.  It could be interesting to explore other senses, such as touch, and taste.

day_2.highlights: Enlighten. Wisdom Creativity. Believe in our own connection with the Universe.
Being able to participate in this important, aligned study feels deeply resonant with everything I’m learning in my bio-energy studies & it’s allowing me to integrate & embody it more fully.
day_2.improvements: The session was beautifully held. The only thing I’d enhance is adding a longer integration window at the end so participants can ground what they’ve received.

day_2.highlights: All! Connection of the group, Breathwork w binural beats and violin, the movement part - incorporating play
day_2.improvements: More clarity of instructions - ex : the questionnaire - i didn’t realize I had to sign into my google account to save it.  Also it sometimes took my out of the experience to have to go to the phone soon thereafter but I can see how this would be necessary.  Could be firmer instructions / directions.

day_2.highlights: The energy in the room, individually and all together was so special and inspiring.
day_2.improvements: I truly have nothing to say here

day_2.emotional_words: SoConfused and think I’m getting this all wrong and filling out the whole thing wrong. Very confusing. Recommend paper next time.
